The crystallographic features of the as-prepared samples were evaluated by XRD patterns (Fig. 1
                     ). In the TiO2 and TiO2/Cdots (0.5 mL) samples, the characteristic peaks of TiO2 are compatible with a tetragonal crystal structure (JCPDS No. 04-0477) [49]. The XRD pattern of Cdots exhibits only a broad peak around 25°, which is assigned to almost amorphous characteristics [50]. In the TiO2/Cdots/Bi4O5Br2 (20%) sample, the characteristic peaks of monoclinic Bi4O5Br2 (JCPDS No. 00-037-0699) are seen beside the TiO2 
                     [51]. It is noted that there are no related peaks of Cdots, owing to the low content [52].
